      "body" : "@dcousens Yes. #7159 contains booleans for `createrawtransaction` and `fundrawtransaction` to opt-int-RBF. Not sure if we want this or if we should go with a new call (something like `alterrawtransaction`). Also the process/workflow how to change the fee of a opt-in-RBF transaction is unclear (could also go over `alterrawtransaction`). And then, there is also the point where we once said we should move the utility-only functions to `bitcoin-tx`, etc.\r\n\r\nThis PR does only add a feature to set the nSequence number per input for `createrawtransaction` and `bitcoin-tx`. This is not directly related to RBF.\r\n\r\nAt least with this PR someone can create a RBF tx without fiddling with the hex-string (good for testing future changes as well).",
